2 QQ-plots v0-5 + tunnings

The QQ-plots for a single trait FEV1pp_utah are shown.

The description of the model versions:

trait ver formula
FEV1pp_utah 0 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global
FEV1pp_utah 1 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + (1|ccenter)
FEV1pp_utah 2 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + pc1 + pc2 + pc3 + pc4
FEV1pp_utah 3 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + pc1 + pc2 + pc3 + pc4 + (1|ccenter)
FEV1pp_utah 4 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + apc1 + apc2 + apc3 + apc4
FEV1pp_utah 5 FEV1pp_utah ~ Age_Enroll + gender + SmokCigNow + ATS_PackYears + acs_global + apc1 + apc2 + apc3 + apc4 + (1|ccenter)

First, we tried different versions 0, 1, 2, 4.

Second, we applied a few additional tunnings:

  • use LRT instead of the Wald test;
  • filter out unrelated individuals (kinship > 0.025);
    • Among 3,300 African-Americans, there are no pairs with kinship > 0.125
    • The threshold 0.025 was used as in http://biorxiv.org/content/early/2016/05/01/036640
    • The number of related individuals (kinship > 0.025) was 117 out of 3,300

4 Principal components

  • PCs on genotypes received from Michael.
  • Ancestry PCs were computed on long ancestry segments
  • Global ancestry esimated as average across all local ancestries
    • Generally, it is not the same as global ancestry estimated by specialized programs
